                      "title":  "The Titanic Conspiracy: The Secret Plot to Sink an Ocean Giant",
                      "description":  "\u003cp\u003eOver a thousand people died when the Titanic sank in 1912. The official story is that it was an accident. This book asks what the full record actually shows.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt examines the documented anomalies. The insurance policy taken out weeks before the voyage. The suspicious passenger list of people who canceled at the last minute. The questions about the ship\u0027s speed despite ice warnings. The insufficient lifeboats that everyone knew about. The behavior of the company in the aftermath. And the theories about whether it was even the Titanic that sank, or its damaged sister ship the Olympic.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSome of this is speculative. Some of it is well-documented. The book is honest about which is which and lets the reader draw their own conclusions from the evidence.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMore than a century later, the Titanic still has unanswered questions. This book asks them directly.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch6 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eTABLE OF CONTENTS\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h6\u003e\u003ch2 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 1: THE DAWN OF THE WHITE STAR EMPIRE\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eRise of White Star from clipper ships to luxury liners under Thomas and Bruce Ismay.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThe 1907 dinner sparking the Olympic-class vision amid Cunard rivalry.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eFinancial strains from IMM merger and the push for grandeur over safety.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\u003ch2 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 2: TWINS IN STEEL: THE BIRTH OF OLYMPIC AND TITANIC\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eConstruction details at Harland and Wolff, including the Arrol Gantry and modular builds.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eEerie similarities in design and subtle differences like porthole counts.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eEfficiency of sister ships raising early suspicions of potential swaps.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\u003ch2 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 3: THE SHADOW OF INSURANCE: FINANCIAL GAMBLES AT SEA\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eMassive policies on Olympic-class exceeding costs, tempting over-insurance.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eWhite Star\u0027s IMM debts and the Ο²¬Θ1 million payout as a financial lifeline.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eLloyd\u0027s syndicates and clauses that blurred risks between the twins.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\u003ch2 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 4: J.P. MORGAN\u0027S INVISIBLE HAND\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eMorgan\u0027s IMM trust swallowing White Star for Atlantic monopoly.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eInfluence on designs, like lifeboat cuts, and operational pressures.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eTies to global banking and pre-war naval conversions of liners.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\u003ch2 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 5: THE FEDERAL RESERVE PLOT THICKENS\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eDebates o