                      "description":  "\u003cp\u003eGermany\u0027s history books have always been written carefully. This one wasn\u0027t.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt covers the parts that tend to get glossed over in classrooms and left out of guided tours. The political violence that preceded the Nazi era and the strange alliances that made it possible. The postwar deals that shaped a nation built partly on silence. The inconvenient facts about what ordinary people knew, when they knew it, and what they chose to do about it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGermany is a country that has confronted its own past more honestly than almost any other. But even that confrontation has limits. This book is about what lies just past those limits.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you think you know German history, you probably know the official version. This is the rest of it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch6 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eTABLE OF CONTENTS\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h6\u003e\u003chr\u003e\u003ch4 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 1: THE BEGINNINGS IN THE DEPTHS OF TIME: PREHISTORIC MYSTERIES AND FORGOTTEN CULTURES\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eIce Age hunters and ritual artifacts\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eTransition to agriculture with Linear Pottery culture\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eMegalithic tombs as sacred places\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eBronze Age treasures and Celtic influences\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eProto-Germanic cultures and astronomical mysteries\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\u003ch4 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 2: THE GERMANS BEYOND THE LEGENDS: RITUALS AND HIDD