                      "title":  "The History of The Persian Empire: From Achaemenids to Sasanians (The History Series)",
                      "description":  "\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan class=\"a-text-bold\"\u003eAt its peak, the Persian Empire was the largest empire the world had ever seen, and it was built on principles that most ancient rulers never considered.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCyrus the Great didn\u0027t just conquer. He issued the world\u0027s first known human rights declaration, freed enslaved peoples, and allowed conquered nations to keep their religions and customs. What he and his successors built across the ancient Near East became a template for how empires could function, for better and for worse. The Achaemenid, Parthian, and Sassanid dynasties that followed added their own chapters to a story that spanned more than a thousand years.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThis book traces the Persian Empire from its earliest origins through its most powerful phases and its eventual transformation under Alexander the Great and the Islamic conquest. It covers the military campaigns, the administrative genius, the artistic legacy, and the clashes with Greece that shaped both civilizations. Every era is brought to life with depth and clarity.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan class=\"a-text-bold\"\u003eWhat you\u0027ll discover inside:\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul class=\"a-unordered-list a-vertical\"\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"a-list-item\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCyrus the Great\u0027s revolutionary approach to empire-building and his legendary conquests\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"a-list-item\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThe Persian Wars with Greece and what they really meant for both civilizations\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"a-list-item\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eDarius and Xerxes and the height of Achaemenid power\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"a-list-item\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eAlexander\u0027s conquest and the transformation of Persian culture into something new\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"a-list-item\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThe Parthian and Sassanid empires and Persia\u0027s enduring influence on the ancient world\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan class=\"a-text-bold\"\u003eReader review:\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"a-text-italic\"\u003e\"I\u0027d only ever heard about Persia as the enemy of the Greeks in movies. This book completely reframed my understanding. Persia was one of the greatest civilizations in human history. Compelling and eye-opening.\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e ΟΔβ²§βÄù Diana F.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThe Persian Empire shaped the ancient world in ways that still resonate today. This book tells its story with the breadth and detail it deserves.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan class=\"a-text-bold\"\u003eOrder your copy now and explore the rise and fall of history\u0027s first great superpower.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e",
