                      "slug":  "the-history-of-croatia",
                      "asin":  "0300246579",
                      "title":  "The History of Croatia: From Illyria to the Habsburgs",
                      "description":  "\u003cp\u003eCroatia spent most of its history being part of something else. The story of how it became a country in its own right is one of the most turbulent in modern Europe.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis book covers the Illyrian and Roman periods, the arrival of Slavic peoples, the medieval Croatian kingdom, centuries under the Habsburgs as a borderland against Ottoman expansion, the South Slav unification movements of the 19th century, the Kingdom of Yugoslavia, the brutal Ustasha state in World War II and the partisan resistance, the communist Yugoslavia under Tito, the 1991 declaration of independence, and the war that followed it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCroatia\u0027s 1990s war is one of the most documented ethnic conflicts in history and one of the least understood outside the region. This book puts it in its proper context.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA small country with a disproportionately large and consequential history.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch6 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eTABLE OF CONTENTS\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h6\u003e\u003chr\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 1: INTRODUCTION, EARLY HUMAN PRESENCE IN THE REGION\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eEarliest human footprints and cave sites\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eFirst stone tools and hunter-gatherer lifestyles\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eEnvironmental factors shaping early settlement\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 2: PREHISTORIC SETTLEMENTS \u0026amp; TRIBAL SOCIETIES\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eShift from nomadic to settled farming communities\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eNeolithic, Copper, and Bronze Age developments\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eFormation of early tribal identities\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 3: THE ROLE OF ILLYRIAN TRIBES\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eOrigins and spread of Illyrian groups\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePolitical and cultural organization\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eInteractions among Illyrian tribes\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 4: GREEK INFLUENCE ON THE EASTERN ADRIATIC\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eFounding of Greek colonies along the coast\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eTrade, cultural, and artistic exchanges\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eLasting Greek impact on local communities\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 5: ROMAN CONQUEST \u0026amp; INTEGRATION\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eMilitary campaigns against Illyrian and local tribes\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eRoman administrative and legal systems\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eUrban development and infrastructure projects\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 6: CHRISTIANITY \u0026amp; THE LATE ROMAN PERIOD\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eSpread of Christian beliefs in Roman Dalmatia\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eChurch organization and early Christian communities\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eShifts in power during the empireΟΔβ²§β³Δs decline\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 7: MIGRATION PERIOD \u0026amp; THE ARRIVAL OF THE CROATS\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eDisruption after the fall of Rome\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=