                      "description":  "\u003cp\u003eHistory is usually told about Hitler. This book is told by him.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDrawing on his actual writings, speeches, and documented statements, this is a first-person narrative reconstruction of his inner world. It covers his youth in Linz and Vienna, his years in the trenches, his obsession with Germany\u0027s humiliation, his rise through Munich beer halls, and the unraveling of everything he built.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eReading it won\u0027t make you sympathize with him. It will make you understand, in a way that dry historical analysis never quite achieves, how a man like this is actually possible. How he thought. What he believed. Why people followed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUnderstanding evil is not the same as excusing it. This book is for readers who believe that understanding it is the only way to prevent it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch6\u003e\u003cspan\u003eProduct Details\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h6\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eDimensions: \u003cstrong\u003e6 ΟÉβÄî 9 inches / 15.24 x 22.86 cm\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCover: \u003cstrong\u003ePaperback\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e",
