                      "description":  "\u003cp\u003eThe Middle Ages lasted a thousand years and most people know it from two things: plague and castles. This book covers what actually happened in between.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt traces the social, economic, and cultural transitions from the fall of Rome through the rise of the medieval church, the feudal system, the Crusades, the Black Death, and the slow unraveling that led to the Renaissance. The focus is on the facts that reveal how different daily life actually was, and how surprisingly modern some medieval institutions and ideas were in comparison to what came before.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou will come away with a much sharper picture of how medieval Europe functioned, why it lasted as long as it did, and what forces eventually brought it to an end. Not a bleak period of darkness. A complicated one worth understanding.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMore was happening in those thousand years than the textbooks let on.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch6 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eTABLE OF CONTENTS\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h6\u003e\u003ch4 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 1: EARLY MIDDLE AGES: THE WORLD AFTER ROME\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCollapse of Roman authority and rise of new Germanic kingdoms\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eMonastic centers preserving knowledge\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eBlend of Roman and tribal customs forming early medieval culture\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\u003ch4 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 2: THE BYZANTINE EMPIRE: A SHINING LIGHT IN THE EAST\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eContinuation of Roman traditions under Eastern emperors\u003c/span\u00