                      "description":  "\u003cp\u003eAsia is home to the oldest civilizations on earth, and some of the most violent episodes in human history. Most of it never makes it into Western textbooks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis book covers the darker chapters. The Mongol conquests that may have killed 10% of the world\u0027s population. The deliberate famines of colonial India. The Nanjing Massacre and the Japanese Imperial Army\u0027s trail across East Asia. The Khmer Rouge genocide in Cambodia. The Cultural Revolution in China. The comfort women of Korea. Histories that deserve to be known.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAsia\u0027s past is vast and complex. This book focuses on the parts that shaped the modern world in ways most people haven\u0027t been properly told about.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThese are not distant abstractions. They are recent history, and they matter for understanding Asia today.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch6 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eTABLE OF CONTENTS\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h6\u003e\u003chr\u003e\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003cb\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/b\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eChapter 1: The Mysterious Indus Valley Civilizations\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eEarly settlements in the Indus River region\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eStrange urban planning, possible rituals, and unknown scripts\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePotential causes of decline and unsettling archaeological finds\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cbr data-mce-bogus=\"1\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch