                      "description":  "\u003cp\u003eGrammar rules get you nowhere fast if you can\u0027t string together a real sentence when it matters. This book gives you 700 phrases that work in actual Frisian conversations.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOrganized by situation and topic, the phrases cover the full range of everyday communication: greetings, asking for help, navigating, shopping, eating out, talking about yourself, expressing opinions, and much more. Each phrase is immediately usable without needing to adapt or conjugate anything. The selection focuses on what people actually say in Friesland, not textbook constructions that sound unnatural to native ears.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou will be able to communicate in Frisian from day one, hold basic conversations, and sound like someone who made a genuine effort to learn the language rather than just defaulting to Dutch. In Friesland, that effort is noticed and appreciated.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e700 phrases. Real situations. Start speaking Frisian today.\u003c/p\u003e",
