pan\u003eTABLE OF CONTENTS\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h6\u003e\n\u003ch3 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\n\u003cspan\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 1: THE ROOTS OF PHILOSOPHICAL THOUGHT ΟΔβ²§βÄ€ ANCIENT CIVILIZATIONS AND MYTHOLOGY\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eEarliest mythological frameworks in Mesopotamia and Egypt\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eHow stories and religious beliefs paved the way for reason-based inquiry\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThe shift from oral tradition to observational thinking\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 2: THE PRE-SOCRATIC ERA AND PHILOSOPHICAL BEGINNINGS\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eRise of natural philosophy in Ionia\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eSearch for fundamental principles by Thales, Anaximander, and Anaximenes\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eDebates on change, permanence, and the nature of reality\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 3: THE LIFE AND TEACHINGS OF SOCRATES\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eSocratic method and the pursuit of ethical living\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eImportance of questioning and self-examination\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThe trial of Socrates and its impact on Athenian thought\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n