n\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 7: ROMAN PHILOSOPHY ΟΔβ²§βÄ€ CICERO, SENECA, AND THE GROWTH OF THOUGHT\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eAdaptation of Greek philosophical schools for Roman values\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCiceroΟΔβ²§β³Δs role in preserving and spreading Greek ideas\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eSenecaΟΔβ²§β³Δs moral insights and Stoic ethics in a practical context\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 8: NEO-PLATONISM AND LATE ANCIENT PHILOSOPHY\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePlotinusΟΔβ²§β³Δs concept of the One and the hierarchical universe\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eStriving for spiritual ascent through contemplation\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eInfluence on early Christian thinkers and later medieval thought\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCHAPTER 9: EARLY MEDIEVAL PHILOSOPHICAL DEVELOPMENTS\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eFusion of Christian doctrine with classical Greek and Roman ideas\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePreservation of knowledge through monastic scholarship\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli role=\"presentation\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eDebates over faith, reason, and divine truth\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch3 dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\u003cspan